CONDITIONS

1. ATTRIBUTION IN SOURCE AND BINARIES
   All copies, modified or unmodified, source or binary, must retain:
     a. This copyright notice.
     b. This license text (or a URL linking to it).
     c. A clear, visible credit: "Built with Lovelang by patel krish"
        OR "Powered by Lovelang (github.com/PATEL-KRISH-0/lovelang)"

   Acceptable placements include: README, NOTICE, about screen, CLI --version
   output, package.json/pyproject.toml description, or similar.

2. ATTRIBUTION IN MODIFIED VERSIONS
   If you distribute a modified version of the Software (fork, patch, derived
   language, compiler rewrite, etc.), you MUST:
     a. Clearly state that your version is a modification of Lovelang.
     b. State the nature of your changes (e.g., in a CHANGES file or header).
     c. Retain attribution to the original: "Based on Lovelang by patel krish"
        (github.com/PATEL-KRISH-0/lovelang).
     d. NOT represent your modified version as the original Lovelang or claim
        original authorship of the unmodified portions.

3. ATTRIBUTION IN ADVERTISING AND PROMOTION
   If you use Lovelang (or a derivative) in a product, service, course,
   article, video, talk, social post, or any public-facing communication that
   describes, promotes, or demonstrates that product, you MUST include a
   clear, readable credit statement. Examples:

     ✅  "Uses Lovelang — github.com/PATEL-KRISH-0/lovelang"
     ✅  "Built with Lovelang by patel krish"
     ✅  "Powered by Lovelang (MIT+Attribution, patel krish)"

   This credit must be:
     - Visible and legible (not hidden in tooltips, white-on-white, or <1pt).
     - Present wherever the product or feature is described to end users.
     - In all paid advertisements where Lovelang is a featured component.

   You do NOT need attribution in:
     - Internal tools never shown to external users.
     - Personal hobby projects that are never published.

4. PATENT GRANT
   Each contributor grants you a perpetual, worldwide, royalty-free, patent
   license to make, use, sell, import, and otherwise transfer the Software.

5. NO TRADEMARK GRANT
   This license does not grant permission to use the name "Lovelang", the
   heart logo, or any associated trademarks for anything other than factual
   attribution required by this license.

